{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Salmon filling","content":["Place eschalot and chilli into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add capers, yoghurt, pepper and eggs and mix <nobr>3 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Add salmon and gently stir to combine.","Preheat oven to 190°C. Spray a baking tray (20 x 30 cm) with oil.","Spray 1 sheet of filo pastry with oil. Line prepared baking tray with oiled pastry, allowing pastry to overlap edges. Spray a second sheet of filo pastry with oil and layer on top of previous sheet. Repeat spraying and layering with 2 more sheets of the pastry. Sprinkle pastry with breadcrumbs and spread with reserved salmon mixture. Fold in any overlapping edges. Spray all remaining 4 sheets of pastry with oil and layer over salmon filling. Tuck in any overlapping edges and score pie with a diamond pattern. Sprinkle with sesame seeds and bake for 18-20 minutes (190°C) until golden and crisp. Clean and dry mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Herb dressing","content":["Place parsley, basil, garlic and salt into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add oil and lemon juice and mix <nobr>5 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Drizzle salmon pie with dressing and serve warm."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Salmon filling","content":["1 eschalot","1 fresh long red chilli, trimmed","1 tbsp pickled capers, drained","200 g Greek-style natural yoghurt","2 pinches ground black pepper","2 eggs","300 - 400 g hot smoked salmon, flaked into bite-size pieces","olive oil spray (see Tip)","8 sheets filo pastry","3 tbsp panko breadcrumbs","2 tsp sesame seeds"]},{"title":"Herb dressing","content":["5 sprigs fresh flat-leaf parsley, leaves only","5 sprigs fresh basil, leaves only","1 garlic clove","2 pinches salt","60 g extra virgin olive oil","20 g lemon juice"]}],"id":"r256215","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/--SxK1uoPNdw\/XZQunh2t58I\/AAAAAAAAcVQ\/Fr